WEBVTT

00:00.066 --> 00:02.434
<i>PREVIOUSLY, ON</i>
<i>SIGNED, SEALED, DELIVERED.</i>

00:02.436 --> 00:03.602
MS. McINERNEY,
I DON'T THINK

00:03.604 --> 00:04.737
YOU'VE BEEN WITH
THIS DEPARTMENT LONG ENOUGH

00:04.739 --> 00:06.138
TO FULLY GRASP
THE EXTENT

00:06.140 --> 00:07.172
TO WHICH WE ARE
COMFORTABLE SHARING.

00:07.174 --> 00:08.272
[SHANE]: SO LAST WEEK,

00:08.274 --> 00:10.509
WHEN YOU TOLD ME THAT
YOUR WIFE LEFT YOU LAST YEAR

00:10.511 --> 00:12.578
AND IS NOW SOMEWHERE AT LARGE
IN PARIS,

00:12.580 --> 00:15.080
THAT WAS SOMEHOW DIFFERENT?

00:17.417 --> 00:19.518
[♪]

00:19.520 --> 00:22.254
[HELICOPTER ROTORS BEATING]

00:27.727 --> 00:29.395
[ROTORS BEATING]

00:33.700 --> 00:36.135
[ANXIOUS VOICES RISING]

00:40.607 --> 00:43.342
[AUTOMATIC GUNFIRE
OVERLAPPING]

00:43.344 --> 00:46.045
[WAKES WITH A GASP]

00:55.789 --> 00:59.158
WHEN I GO TO COLLEGE,
I'M ONLY TAKING MY BACKPACK.

01:01.594 --> 01:04.296
[♪]

01:46.739 --> 01:49.241
♪ SEND ME LOVE EVERY DAY

01:49.243 --> 01:51.844
♪ AND SEND ME ON MY WAY

01:51.846 --> 01:55.481
♪ DELIVER ME
JUST DELIVER ME ♪

01:57.584 --> 01:59.585
[OLIVER]: AND THEN WE WERE

01:59.587 --> 02:00.686
FORCED TO ACKNOWLEDGE--

02:00.688 --> 02:02.488
AS DIFFICULT
AS IT IS TO ADMIT--

02:02.490 --> 02:04.256
SOME THINGS DEFY DELIVERY.

02:04.258 --> 02:06.158
WELL, YOU DID
EVERYTHING YOU COULD.

02:06.160 --> 02:07.392
AND, UH, WHO KNOWS?

02:07.394 --> 02:09.595
ONE DAY, SOMEONE
MAY WALK IN HERE,

02:09.597 --> 02:12.197
LOOKING FOR A GRIZZLY
WITH INSUFFICIENT POSTAGE

02:12.199 --> 02:14.466
AND NO FORWARDING
ADDRESS.

02:14.468 --> 02:15.868
WE CAN ONLY HOPE, HMM?

02:15.870 --> 02:17.769
WE TAKE
GOOD CARE OF HIM.

02:17.771 --> 02:19.571
WE DECORATE HIM
ON HOLIDAYS.

02:19.573 --> 02:20.672
DON'T BEAT YOURSELF UP.

02:20.674 --> 02:22.307
ONE WAYWARD BEAR

02:22.309 --> 02:24.676
IS NOT GOING TO AFFECT
YOUR PERFORMANCE RATING.

02:24.678 --> 02:27.546
WHEN MIGHT WE EXPECT
YOUR FINAL REPORT?

02:27.548 --> 02:30.315
OLIVER,
COULD I HAVE A... WORD?

02:30.317 --> 02:32.217
MS. McINERNEY,

02:32.219 --> 02:33.852
MS. CAPODIAMONTE HERE
WAS JUST COMPLETING

02:33.854 --> 02:37.256
MY ANNUAL SECTION LEADER
PERFORMANCE EVALUATION.

02:37.258 --> 02:40.159
"COMPLETING"?
OH, NO, DARLING!

02:40.161 --> 02:41.793
I DIDN'T GET WHERE I AM
BY CUTTING CORNERS.

02:41.795 --> 02:43.228
OH, OF COURSE!
I DIDN'T MEAN TO IMPLY--

02:43.230 --> 02:45.164
I WANT TO CRAWL

02:45.166 --> 02:47.199
INTO THAT MYSTERIOUS
LITTLE MIND OF YOURS

02:47.201 --> 02:48.600
AND FIND OUT
WHAT MAKES THIS PLACE

02:48.602 --> 02:49.601
TICK-TICK-TICK!

02:49.603 --> 02:51.336
HAH! IT'LL BE FUN.

02:51.338 --> 02:53.672
I... LOOK FORWARD TO THAT.

02:53.674 --> 02:56.575
MS. McINERNEY, ALL CAUGHT UP
AND FINISHED ON TIME, I SEE.

02:56.577 --> 02:57.676
NATURALLY.

02:57.678 --> 02:59.778
WELL, I'M OFF
TO REHEARSAL.

02:59.780 --> 03:02.614
UH, HOW IS
THE NEW SHOW GOING?

03:02.616 --> 03:04.917
WELL, I'M ONLY AN UNDERSTUDY,
BUT, UH...

03:04.919 --> 03:07.920
THE MAYOR OF MUNCHKINLAND
MAY BE CALLED UP FOR JURY DUTY!

03:07.922 --> 03:09.755
AND EVEN BETTER--

03:09.757 --> 03:12.457
MRS. KIPPERMAN'S BURSITIS
IS ACTING UP,

03:12.459 --> 03:14.493
SO I MAY BE
THE "WICKED WITCH OF THE WEST"

03:14.495 --> 03:15.727
BY SUNDAY!

03:16.829 --> 03:17.829
I GUESS
IT'S NEVER TOO LATE

03:17.831 --> 03:18.864
TO PURSUE YOUR DREAMS.

03:18.866 --> 03:20.299
ALL THE WAY

03:20.301 --> 03:22.334
TO THE BROOMFIELD COMMUNITY
CHILDREN'S THEATRE.

03:22.336 --> 03:24.870
AND MAY WE ASSUME
THAT YOUR DREAM IS

03:24.872 --> 03:27.506
TO RE-DIRECT THE LAST ENVELOPE
IN THAT BOX

03:27.508 --> 03:28.574
BEFORE YOU LEAVE TONIGHT?

03:28.576 --> 03:30.342
[SIGHING]
COME ON, OLIVER.

03:30.344 --> 03:32.644
NORMAN, WHY MUST THAT BOX
BE EMPTIED TONIGHT?

03:32.646 --> 03:34.846
UH, LAST DAY
OF THE MONTH

03:34.848 --> 03:36.215
IS "IMPOSSIBLY RIPPED
AND MANGLED DAY,"

03:36.217 --> 03:37.983
AND WE CAN'T START
A NEW MONTH

03:37.985 --> 03:40.686
WITH MANGLED LEFTOVERS.

03:40.688 --> 03:43.789
OKAY. BUT WE WORKED
THROUGH LUNCH AND I'M HUNGRY--

03:43.791 --> 03:46.425
WOW. ALMOST HALF
THIS ENVELOPE'S MISSING.

03:46.427 --> 03:47.726
HMM. NOTHING LEGIBLE,

03:47.728 --> 03:49.294
EXCEPT "TO WHOM
IT MAY CONCERN..."

03:49.296 --> 03:50.562
"TO WHOM
IT MAY CONCERN?"

03:50.564 --> 03:51.862
WE COULD BE HERE ALL NIGHT!

03:51.864 --> 03:53.398
PROBABLY. THIS POSTMARK'S
FOUR YEARS OLD.

03:53.400 --> 03:54.967
SEE?

03:54.969 --> 03:56.435
IT'S TOO LATE TO MAKE
A DIFFERENCE ANYWAY.

03:56.437 --> 03:57.569
YOU THINK SO?

03:57.571 --> 03:58.737
BECAUSE...

03:58.739 --> 04:01.273
THERE'S ANOTHER LETTER
INSIDE THIS ONE.

04:01.275 --> 04:03.242
CONSIDERING
THE CONDITION OF THE ENVELOPE,

04:03.244 --> 04:04.610
I'D SAY
IT'S SOMETHING OF A MIRACLE

04:04.612 --> 04:06.311
THAT IT DIDN'T FALL OUT.

04:06.313 --> 04:07.512
ARE WE IN THE HABIT
OF IGNORING MIRACLES?

04:07.514 --> 04:08.614
[BOTH]: NO.

04:08.616 --> 04:10.949
NO. IN FACT, I'M ASSUMING

04:10.951 --> 04:13.318
THERE IS A DIFFERENCE
TO BE MADE HERE.

04:13.320 --> 04:15.921
FINE. CAN WE JUST PLEASE
MAKE A DIFFERENCE OVER DINNER?

04:15.923 --> 04:16.989
I'LL EVEN BUY.

04:16.991 --> 04:17.956
IT IS ALL-YOU-CAN-EAT
SALAD BAR NIGHT

04:17.958 --> 04:18.957
AT THE MAILBOX GRILLE.

04:18.959 --> 04:21.360
PERFECT.

04:22.495 --> 04:23.762
I LOVE SALAD BARS!

04:23.764 --> 04:26.598
PICKLES, OLIVES,
SUNFLOWER SEEDS...

04:27.967 --> 04:30.569
RITA? AREN'T,
UM, YOU HUNGRY?

04:30.571 --> 04:32.571
I WAS JUST THINKING
ABOUT THERESA.

04:32.573 --> 04:34.740
IF YOU'RE WORRIED ABOUT
MY PERFORMANCE EVALUATION,

04:34.742 --> 04:36.508
I'M FEELING PRETTY CONFIDENT.

04:36.510 --> 04:37.609
SO FAR.

04:37.611 --> 04:38.677
HE ALWAYS GETS

04:38.679 --> 04:39.745
THE HIGHEST SCORES
OF ANYBODY--

04:39.747 --> 04:40.812
98s, 99s.

04:40.814 --> 04:41.847
I GOT A 95 ONCE.

04:41.849 --> 04:43.348
IT STILL HAUNTS ME.

04:43.350 --> 04:46.718
WOW! UH, COULD SOMEONE GRAB
THE TABASCO SAUCE?

04:46.720 --> 04:48.587
I WASN'T THINKING
ABOUT THE EVALUATION.

04:48.589 --> 04:49.921
I WAS THINKING ABOUT

04:49.923 --> 04:52.858
WHAT IT MUST BE LIKE
TO <i>BE</i> THERESA.

04:52.860 --> 04:57.596
I MEAN,
SHE IS A POSTAL <i>LEGEND.</i>

04:57.598 --> 04:58.830
MM. FOUR
POSTAL COMMENDATIONS

04:58.832 --> 05:00.532
SIX SERVICE AWARDS,
NOT TO MENTION

05:00.534 --> 05:01.867
"MISS SPECIAL
DELIVERY" 1969.

05:01.869 --> 05:03.068
[RITA]: THAT'S WHAT I MEAN!

05:03.070 --> 05:04.836
I MEAN, SHE HAD IT ALL!

05:04.838 --> 05:06.538
BUT IT WASN'T
HER DREAM.

05:06.540 --> 05:08.340
WELL, SHE DID ADMIT
HER LIFE'S DREAM

05:08.342 --> 05:09.474
WAS TO BE
ON THE STAGE.

05:09.476 --> 05:10.676
AND IF MRS. KIPPERMAN'S BURSITIS
KEEPS UP,

05:10.678 --> 05:11.877
THEN SHE WILL BE.

05:11.879 --> 05:13.345
COULD YOU PASS
THE SALT AND PEPPER, PLEASE?

05:13.347 --> 05:15.080
I GUESS IT'S JUST
NEVER TOO LATE,

05:15.082 --> 05:16.782
LIKE YOU SAID,
NORMAN.

05:16.784 --> 05:18.450
DO YOU HAVE A DREAM

05:18.452 --> 05:19.951
YOU'D LIKE TO SHARE
WITH US, RITA?

05:19.953 --> 05:20.919
YES!

05:20.921 --> 05:22.888
[INHALES] OH, I--

05:22.890 --> 05:24.623
NO.

05:24.625 --> 05:26.892
YES, I--
UM, DO. UM...

05:26.894 --> 05:29.394
BUT I'M NOT READY
TO SHARE IT, NOT YET.

05:29.396 --> 05:30.394
I HAD A DREAM ONCE.

05:30.396 --> 05:31.430
YOU KNOW, THE KIND
YOU ACTUALLY REMEMBER

05:31.432 --> 05:32.597
WHEN YOU WAKE UP?

05:32.599 --> 05:34.499
IT WAS ABOUT CHEESE.
CHEESE WITH FEET.

05:34.501 --> 05:37.069
OKAY. SO I THINK WE SHOULD OPEN
THAT LETTER NOW.

05:37.071 --> 05:39.504
-WHAT DO YOU SAY, OLIVER?
-YES. LET'S.

05:39.506 --> 05:41.640
CHEESE... REALLY?

05:41.642 --> 05:42.974
MM-HMM.

05:42.976 --> 05:45.744
"TO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN..."

05:46.879 --> 05:48.847
"MY NAME IS SAMILA.

05:48.849 --> 05:50.082
"I AM 18 YEARS OLD

05:50.084 --> 05:52.451
"AND I LIVE
IN SEATTLE, WASHINGTON.

05:52.453 --> 05:53.819
"I HAVE TRIED EVERYTHING.

05:53.821 --> 05:56.054
"I'VE CALLED ALL
YOUR OFFICIAL PHONE NUMBERS,

05:56.056 --> 05:57.823
"I'VE CHECKED
ALL SORTS OF ONLINE WEBSITES,

05:57.825 --> 06:00.425
"AND SEARCHED
DOZENS OF ARCHIVES,

06:00.427 --> 06:01.660
"BUT NOTHING HAS WORKED,

06:01.662 --> 06:03.962
"SO I AM TURNING TO YOU,
WHOEVER OPENS THIS,

06:03.964 --> 06:06.998
"AND I AM HOPING YOU WILL
CARE ENOUGH TO HELP ME.

06:07.000 --> 06:10.769
"I AM TRYING TO FIND
THE MAN WHO SAVED MY LIFE...

06:10.771 --> 06:13.605
AND CHANGED IT FOREVER."

06:18.778 --> 06:19.911
WOW.

06:19.913 --> 06:21.680
WHAT'S THE PAPER
THAT IT AS CLIPPED TO?

06:21.682 --> 06:22.948
IS THAT SOME SORT OF
GOVERNMENT FORM?

06:22.950 --> 06:25.784
A "REQUEST FOR
MILITARY SERVICE INFORMATION."

06:25.786 --> 06:29.087
AND A PERSONAL CARD
ADDRESSED TO "BUZZ."

06:29.089 --> 06:30.889
"I NEVER FOUND OUT
WHAT EVER HAP..."

06:30.891 --> 06:33.458
UH, IT'S DAMAGED HERE.

06:33.460 --> 06:34.826
"IF YOU LOCATE HIM,

06:34.828 --> 06:37.529
"PLEASE GIVE HIM
THE ENCLOSED CARD.

06:37.531 --> 06:38.730
"HE NEEDS TO KNOW

06:38.732 --> 06:40.432
SOMETHING REALLY IMPORTANT
THAT COULD..."

06:40.434 --> 06:42.968
SOMETHING... UH, SOMETHING...

06:42.970 --> 06:44.002
I GUESS THAT'S WHY
THEY CALL THEM

06:44.004 --> 06:45.070
"HOPELESSLY MANGLED."

06:45.072 --> 06:46.571
IT'S NOT HOPELESS.

06:46.573 --> 06:48.740
WELL, WHAT IS IT
THAT HE NEEDS TO KNOW?

06:48.742 --> 06:50.108
IT'S GOTTA BE IN THIS.

06:50.110 --> 06:52.944
"ALL THIS TIME,
I'VE DREAMED I'D GET THE CHANCE

06:52.946 --> 06:54.679
"TO TELL HIM
HOW IT ALL ENDED,

06:54.681 --> 06:58.717
"BUT I CAN'T,
WITHOUT YOUR HELP.

06:58.719 --> 07:01.853
"I ONLY WISH
I KNEW HIS REAL NAME.

07:01.855 --> 07:05.123
I JUST ALWAYS CALLED HIM
'BUZZ'."

07:06.492 --> 07:09.895
"HOW IT ALL ENDED."
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

07:11.063 --> 07:13.799
IS THERE ANY SALSA?
OR MUSTARD?

07:13.801 --> 07:15.767
OH.

07:15.769 --> 07:17.469
UH, MS. McINERNEY,

07:17.471 --> 07:20.071
PUTTING THAT MANY CONDIMENTS
ON A SALAD CAN'T BE HEALTHY.

07:20.073 --> 07:21.907
BESIDES, WHAT
YOU'RE DOING TO THAT SALAD...

07:21.909 --> 07:23.008
IT'S DISCONCERTING.

07:23.010 --> 07:24.810
I SAY WE OPEN
THE NOTE FOR BUZZ.

07:24.812 --> 07:26.178
[OLIVER]: ABSOLUTELY NOT.

07:26.180 --> 07:27.913
YOU SAID THAT YOU WANTED
TO MAKE A DIFFERENCE,

07:27.915 --> 07:29.213
BUT NOW THAT WE'RE HERE,

07:29.215 --> 07:30.882
IT'S ALL JUST
BACK TO BUSINESS AS USUAL.

07:30.884 --> 07:32.818
EXCUSE ME.
COULD I HAVE SALSA, PLEASE?

07:32.820 --> 07:34.753
YOU SAID YOU WANTED A SALAD,
BUT THAT'S A SCIENCE EXPERIMENT.

07:34.755 --> 07:37.055
OH, AND ALL YOUR TALK ABOUT
NOT IGNORING MIRACLES,

07:37.057 --> 07:39.055
BUT, REALLY,
YOU JUST WANTED TO GET

07:39.057 --> 07:41.092
ALL THE HOPELESSLY MANGLED
LETTERS DONE ON SCHEDULE.

07:41.094 --> 07:42.192
I BELIEVE IN MIRACLES.

07:42.194 --> 07:43.728
I ALSO BELIEVE
IN STAYING ON SCHEDULE.

07:43.730 --> 07:45.197
I BELIEVE
WE HAVE MADE A DIFFERENCE.

07:45.199 --> 07:46.531
WE HAVE GATHERED
ENOUGH INFORMATION

07:46.533 --> 07:47.966
TO SEND THAT ON

07:47.968 --> 07:49.835
-TO THE LIKELY ADDRESSEE.
-AND THAT IS?

07:49.837 --> 07:51.803
UH, PROBABLY THE ARMY.
FORT PLATTE.

07:51.805 --> 07:52.704
EXCELLENT.

07:52.706 --> 07:54.773
THAT'S
WHERE IT'LL GO.

07:54.775 --> 07:57.008
SHALL WE
GET THE CHECK?

07:57.010 --> 07:58.777
OLIVER.

07:58.779 --> 08:00.645
WHAT?

08:00.647 --> 08:01.645
THE ONLY PERSON

08:01.647 --> 08:04.149
THAT WE KNOW THAT LETTER
IS ADDRESSED TO FOR SURE

08:04.151 --> 08:06.084
IS "TO WHOM IT MAY CONCERN."
REMEMBER?

08:06.086 --> 08:07.586
"WHOEVER OPENS THIS"?

08:07.588 --> 08:08.987
WHY WOULD YOU TAKE

08:08.989 --> 08:11.690
SOMETHING SO SIMPLE AND ADD
UNNECESSARY ELEMENTS, HMM?

08:11.692 --> 08:13.825
IS HE TALKING ABOUT
THE LETTER OR THE SALAD?

08:13.827 --> 08:15.527
DO YOU REALLY THINK
THERE'S A BUREAUCRAT

08:15.529 --> 08:17.062
IN THE MILITARY THAT CAN DO
YOUR JOB BETTER THAN YOU?

08:17.064 --> 08:18.964
NO. AND I WOULDN'T
PRESUME TO DO THEIRS.

08:18.966 --> 08:21.666
THAT'S WHY WE'RE GONNA FORWARD
ALL THIS BY U.S. MAIL

08:21.668 --> 08:22.968
TO THE U.S. ARMY, TOMORROW.

08:22.970 --> 08:26.137
FINE. I WILL TAKE CARE OF IT
AS SOON AS I GET IN.

08:26.139 --> 08:28.573
NOT ON YOUR TINTYPE,
MS. McINERNEY.

08:30.977 --> 08:33.245
PLEASE...
STEP AWAY FROM THE SALAD.

08:36.115 --> 08:37.816
[WHISPERS]:
WHAT'S A TINTYPE?

08:37.818 --> 08:39.784
I'LL TELL YOU LATER.

08:41.754 --> 08:44.189
[♪]

08:45.858 --> 08:50.161
IS THIS OLIVER'S REFRIGERATOR,
OR THE GROUP REFRIGERATOR?

08:50.163 --> 08:52.697
OH. IT'S OLIVER'S.

08:52.699 --> 08:54.032
THAT HE...

08:54.034 --> 08:55.934
SHARES
WITH THE GROUP.

08:55.936 --> 08:57.569
AND NORMAN,

08:57.571 --> 09:00.839
I'LL NEED A BRIEF SUMMARY
OF YOUR STAMP-RECOVERY DUTIES.

09:00.841 --> 09:02.841
OH! I DON'T KNOW
WHERE TO START.

09:02.843 --> 09:05.610
WHERE DOES ONE START,
NORMAN, DARLING?

09:05.612 --> 09:06.878
YOU'RE A CIPHER!

09:06.880 --> 09:08.847
JUST FULL OF SURPRISES,
AREN'T YOU?

09:08.849 --> 09:10.815
AND RITA.

09:10.817 --> 09:13.118
YOU ARE
A BEAUTIFUL LITTLE ONION,

09:13.120 --> 09:14.853
BEGGING TO BE PEELED.

09:14.855 --> 09:16.221
[OLIVER]:
GOOD MORNING, EVERYONE.

09:16.223 --> 09:17.321
AH, MS. CAPODIAMONTE.

09:17.323 --> 09:20.725
HOW LOVELY TO SEE YOU AGAIN,
HERE, THIS MORNING.

09:20.727 --> 09:22.827
AGAIN.

09:22.829 --> 09:24.162
PERFECT TIMING, OLIVER.

09:24.164 --> 09:27.666
I NEED MORE CLARIFICATION
ON WORKSPACE.

09:27.668 --> 09:28.833
WORKSPACE?

09:28.835 --> 09:29.901
YES. WE REQUIRE

09:29.903 --> 09:32.771
WORKSPACE
THAT IS APPROPRIATE FOR,

09:32.773 --> 09:34.639
AND ADEQUATE TO, THE TASK.

09:34.641 --> 09:37.943
UH, WELL,
THIS IS MY DESK HERE.

09:37.945 --> 09:41.079
NORMAN HAS BEEN VERY HAPPY
OVER THERE,

09:41.081 --> 09:42.179
AND RITA, OF COURSE,

09:42.181 --> 09:45.250
IS OUR FIRST LINE OF DEFENSE,
OVER IN "INCOMING."

09:45.252 --> 09:46.651
AND, UH,
WHERE DOES SHANE WORK?

09:48.087 --> 09:49.721
MS. McINERNEY?

09:49.723 --> 09:51.256
WELL, MS. McINERNEY IS...

09:51.258 --> 09:53.124
STILL...

09:53.126 --> 09:54.292
SOMEWHAT NEW.

09:54.294 --> 09:57.028
SHE MUST WORK
SOMEWHERE IN HERE. HMM?

09:58.264 --> 10:01.666
I... WORK EVERYWHERE.

10:01.668 --> 10:04.736
MR. O'TOOLE DISPATCHES ME
WHEREVER I'M NEEDED.

10:04.738 --> 10:05.971
I-- I MOVE.

10:05.973 --> 10:08.306
I FLOAT.
HAVE LAPTOP, WILL TRAVEL.

10:08.308 --> 10:09.606
TEMPORARILY,
OF COURSE.

10:09.608 --> 10:12.043
IN FACT, NORMAN HAS
RECENTLY BEEN CHARGED

10:12.045 --> 10:14.646
WITH CREATING
A DEDICATED,

10:14.648 --> 10:17.082
YET FLOATING WORKSPACE
FOR MS. McINERNEY.

10:17.084 --> 10:20.652
YES. THAT'S...
THAT'S RIGHT.

10:20.654 --> 10:21.786
AND IN THE MEANTIME,

10:21.788 --> 10:23.855
I-I WORK A LOT
IN THE FIELD.

10:23.857 --> 10:25.724
UH, IN FACT,

10:25.726 --> 10:30.128
THERE IS A RATHER CRITICAL
PIECE OF MANGLED MAIL

10:30.130 --> 10:33.698
THAT REQUIRES PERSONAL DELIVERY
TO FORT PLATTE.

10:33.700 --> 10:35.166
MR. O'TOOLE HAS

10:35.168 --> 10:37.969
TAUGHT ME SO MUCH
ABOUT GOING THE EXTRA MILE.

10:37.971 --> 10:40.238
WELL, I CAN'T THINK
OF A BETTER MENTOR.

10:40.240 --> 10:41.306
[SHANE]: OH, NEITHER CAN I!

10:41.308 --> 10:42.406
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

10:42.408 --> 10:45.243
BUT YOU KNOW, I'M NOT
QUITE READY TO GO SOLO YET.

10:45.245 --> 10:47.812
YOU COMING,
MR. O'TOOLE?

10:47.814 --> 10:49.981
[♪]

10:52.918 --> 10:55.420
WELL...

10:55.422 --> 10:57.288
CARRY ON.

10:59.291 --> 11:01.860
[♪]

11:11.137 --> 11:12.303
[QUIET BACKGROUND CHATTER]

11:12.305 --> 11:15.974
YOU'RE REALLY MAKING
TOO MUCH OF THIS.

11:15.976 --> 11:17.342
HOW COULD I MAKE
TOO MUCH ABOUT

11:17.344 --> 11:19.778
YOUR SHOCKING ATTEMPT
AT BLACKMAIL BACK THERE?

11:19.780 --> 11:20.945
"BLACKMAIL"?

11:20.947 --> 11:22.447
I DID YOU A FAVOR!

11:22.449 --> 11:23.748
SHE WAS GONNA
TAKE OFF POINTS

11:23.750 --> 11:25.016
YOUR PRECIOUS
PERFORMANCE EVALUATION

11:25.018 --> 11:26.451
BECAUSE I DON'T
HAVE A DESK!

11:26.453 --> 11:28.019
WHAT WILL
RITA AND NORMAN THINK

11:28.021 --> 11:30.021
NOW THAT THEY'VE SEEN ME
SO BRAZENLY MANIPULATED?

11:30.023 --> 11:32.057
OH! FOR HEAVEN'S SAKE.

11:32.059 --> 11:33.191
[FUMING SIGH]

11:33.193 --> 11:34.893
THE VERY FABRIC

11:34.895 --> 11:36.428
OF OUR EXISTENCE
AS AN EFFECTIVE UNIT

11:36.430 --> 11:38.163
HAS BEEN FRAYED,
AND FOR WHAT?

11:39.465 --> 11:41.066
FOR SAMILA!

11:41.068 --> 11:43.234
BECAUSE SOMEONE NAMED BUZZ
SAVED HER LIFE ONCE.

11:43.236 --> 11:44.869
AND WHO KNOWS?

11:44.871 --> 11:47.439
MAYBE SHE'S TRYING TO SAVE HIS.

11:50.409 --> 11:52.143
OLIVER O'TOOLE?

11:55.147 --> 11:57.182
U.S. POST OFFICE?

11:57.184 --> 11:59.217
UH, YES.
DEAD LETTER DIVISION.

11:59.219 --> 12:01.786
WE SPECIALIZE IN
LETTERS THAT REQUIRE--

12:01.788 --> 12:03.288
THIS IS A FORM
REQUESTING INFORMATION

12:03.290 --> 12:04.823
ON SOMEONE
NAMED "BUZZ"

12:04.825 --> 12:06.858
AND THIS IS
THE COVER LETTER.

12:06.860 --> 12:08.326
AS YOU CAN SEE,
IT'S QUITE DAMAGED.

12:08.328 --> 12:09.427
[OLIVER]:
IT HAPPENS SOMETIMES.

12:09.429 --> 12:11.362
UH, RARELY.
WE APOLOGIZE.

12:11.364 --> 12:13.131
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY OF THESE
GET FILLED OUT

12:13.133 --> 12:15.400
AND SENT HERE EVERY DAY?

12:15.402 --> 12:17.102
VETERANS LOOKING
FOR OLD BUDDIES,

12:17.104 --> 12:19.137
GIRLFRIENDS
LOOKING FOR EX-BOYFRIENDS,

12:19.139 --> 12:20.905
EX-WIVES LOOKING FOR MONEY.

12:20.907 --> 12:22.307
BUT THIS ONE
IS DIFFERENT,

12:22.309 --> 12:23.374
IF YOU'LL JUST READ IT,

12:23.376 --> 12:25.477
YOU'LL SEE WHERE
SAMILA MENTIONS--

12:25.479 --> 12:27.345
"SAMILA"?
SOUNDS MIDDLE EASTERN.

12:27.347 --> 12:29.481
WERE YOU IN THE MIDDLE EAST?

12:29.483 --> 12:32.784
I WAS EVERYWHERE.

12:32.786 --> 12:34.185
LOOK, YOU DID YOUR DUTY.

12:34.187 --> 12:36.488
YOU DELIVERED THE LETTER,
OR WHAT'S LEFT OF IT.

12:36.490 --> 12:37.355
SO DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

12:37.357 --> 12:38.223
OH, THERE'S ANOTHER--

12:38.225 --> 12:40.325
NOPE. UM, THAT'S IT!

12:40.327 --> 12:41.960
THANK YOU

12:41.962 --> 12:43.795
FOR YOUR TIME,
CAPTAIN.

12:44.930 --> 12:46.831
YEAH. WELL,
THANKS FOR TRYING.

12:46.833 --> 12:49.033
AND THANK YOU,
CAPTAIN, FOR SERVING.

12:50.136 --> 12:52.504
[♪]

12:53.973 --> 12:55.106
AT WHAT POINT
DO YOU PLAN

12:55.108 --> 12:57.041
TO STOP LYING
TO GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS?

12:57.043 --> 12:59.244
DO YOU HONESTLY THINK THAT
THAT MAN BACK THERE

12:59.246 --> 13:01.012
WAS ACTUALLY GOING TO
READ THIS LETTER?

13:01.014 --> 13:03.181
AND IF HE DID,
EVEN CARE WHAT IT SAYS?

13:04.884 --> 13:05.984
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

13:05.986 --> 13:08.353
WHAT IS IT YOU ALWAYS SAY?

13:08.355 --> 13:10.321
"PUTTING A STAMP
ON THE LETTER

13:10.323 --> 13:11.823
AND SENDING IT OUT THERE
INTO THE WORLD--"

13:11.825 --> 13:13.124
"...IS AN ACT OF FAITH."

13:14.260 --> 13:15.794
SO IF YOU WANT TO GO BACK
IN THERE

13:15.796 --> 13:17.929
AND PUT YOUR FAITH--
AND SAMILA'S--

13:17.931 --> 13:20.331
IN THAT PILE OF
GOVERNMENT RED TAPE,

13:20.333 --> 13:21.566
WELL, YOU BE MY GUEST.

13:21.568 --> 13:23.802
BUT AS FOR ME...

13:24.904 --> 13:28.139
I'M PUTTING MY FAITH
IN YOU.

13:32.478 --> 13:34.012
YOU CAN BE

13:34.014 --> 13:36.381
VERY PERSUASIVE,
MS. McINERNEY.

13:37.516 --> 13:39.818
OR BRAZENLY MANIPULATIVE.

13:41.353 --> 13:43.488
[♪]

13:45.991 --> 13:47.158
I KNOW THIS IS

13:47.160 --> 13:48.960
PUSHING THE ENVELOPE,
SO TO SPEAK--

13:48.962 --> 13:51.496
IT MIGHT FALL UNDER
THE LARGER DEFINITION

13:51.498 --> 13:53.198
OF "SPECIAL HANDLING."

13:53.200 --> 13:56.134
SOMETHING THAT WE LIKE TO
CALL "A LICENSE TO DELIVER."

13:56.136 --> 13:57.869
-THAT WAS NORMAN'S IDEA.
-OH!

14:05.177 --> 14:07.312
[♪]

14:11.417 --> 14:13.251
"DEAR BUZZ--

14:13.253 --> 14:14.352
"THIS IS...

14:14.354 --> 14:16.354
"SAMILA.

14:16.356 --> 14:17.889
"SAMMY.

14:17.891 --> 14:19.991
"I HOPE YOU REMEMBER ME,

14:19.993 --> 14:22.393
"BECAUSE
I'VE NEVER FORGOTTEN YOU.

14:22.395 --> 14:26.197
I HAVE SO MANY THINGS
TO THANK YOU FOR--"

14:26.199 --> 14:27.866
[OVERLAPPING WITH SAMILA]:
"BUT FIRST..."

14:27.868 --> 14:30.134
[SAMILA]: <i>I GUESS I SHOULD</i>
<i>THANK YOU FOR THE SOCKS.</i>

14:31.170 --> 14:35.206
[♪]

14:37.543 --> 14:39.510
DID SHE SEND
ANY DECENT MOVIES?

14:39.512 --> 14:41.613
UM... <i>MISSION</i>
<i>IMPOSSIBLE 1,</i>

14:41.615 --> 14:43.481
MISSION IMPOSSIBLE 2.

14:45.885 --> 14:49.487
SOCKS, AND...
A PILLOWCASE?

14:49.489 --> 14:51.222
[SCOFFS] THANKS, MOM.

14:51.224 --> 14:52.523
THAT'S GREAT,
'CAUSE, YOU KNOW,

14:52.525 --> 14:53.992
IF THEY GAVE US PILLOWS,
YOU'D BE SET.

14:53.994 --> 14:55.894
OH, WAIT! BROWNIES!

14:55.896 --> 14:57.194
[SAMILA, WRITING]:
<i>I REMEMBER</i>

14:57.196 --> 14:59.097
<i>WHEN THE SOLDIERS</i>
<i>FIRST CAME TO KAMDESH,</i>

14:59.099 --> 15:02.600
<i>SOME OF MY FRIENDS</i>
<i>WERE AFRAID OF THE AMERICANS...</i>

15:02.602 --> 15:07.138
<i>BUT I REMEMBER THE FIRST TIME</i>
<i>I MET ONE OF THEM.</i>

15:07.140 --> 15:09.173
<i>IT WAS YOU.</i>

15:09.175 --> 15:10.174
YOU LIKE THESE?

15:13.679 --> 15:16.314
MY MOM MADE THEM FOR ME.

15:17.549 --> 15:18.983
SHE ALWAYS MAKES THEM
TOO SMALL.

15:18.985 --> 15:20.184
YOU WANT THEM?

15:22.488 --> 15:24.389
IT'S OKAY.

15:26.325 --> 15:29.327
[♪]

15:30.663 --> 15:32.630
YOU GOTTA
BE CAREFUL, BUZZ.

15:32.632 --> 15:34.299
THEY USE KIDS LIKE THIS
TO CARRY BOMBS.

15:35.401 --> 15:37.568
I CAN'T LIVE
LIKE THAT, CAM.

15:41.106 --> 15:42.674
WHAT'S THIS?

15:42.676 --> 15:43.608
YOU WANNA TRADE?

15:43.610 --> 15:46.044
<i>PAKOL.</i>

15:46.046 --> 15:48.279
<i>PAKOL?</i>

15:48.281 --> 15:49.480
"PAKOL." [CHUCKLES]

15:49.482 --> 15:51.249
OKAY, WHATEVER THAT MEANS.

15:51.251 --> 15:52.550
IT PROBABLY MEANS "BOMB."

15:52.552 --> 15:54.319
[SAMILA STARTS LAUGHING]

15:54.321 --> 15:55.987
[SAMILA]:
<i>"PAKOL" MEANS "HAT."</i>

15:55.989 --> 15:57.588
<i>IT WAS MY FATHER'S.</i>

15:57.590 --> 15:59.290
<i>IT WAS ALL I HAD OF HIM.</i>

15:59.292 --> 16:01.993
<i>YOU REMINDED ME OF HIM.</i>

16:01.995 --> 16:03.393
<i>YOU HAD HIS LAUGH.</i>

16:03.395 --> 16:08.266
AND I KNEW YOU WOULD BE THE ONE
<i>TO MAKE MY DREAM COME TRUE.</i>

16:08.268 --> 16:10.001
THANK YOU.

16:10.003 --> 16:12.070
<i>DO YOU</i>
<i>REMEMBER THE PILLOWCASE?</i>

16:12.072 --> 16:14.172
SO THIS IS
OUR LANGUAGE.

16:14.174 --> 16:15.673
OKAY, SAMMY.
"A" IS FOR...?

16:15.675 --> 16:19.043
"AF-GHAN-IS-TAN."

16:19.045 --> 16:20.178
AND "B" IS FOR...?

16:20.180 --> 16:21.245
"BUZZ."

16:21.247 --> 16:23.281
"C" IS

16:23.283 --> 16:25.149
"COLO-RADO."

16:25.151 --> 16:26.317
AMERICA.

16:26.319 --> 16:27.717
PLACE YOUR HOME.

16:27.719 --> 16:29.153
<i>I BEGGED YOU</i>
<i>TO TEACH ME TO READ.</i>

16:29.155 --> 16:31.756
<i>I COULD TELL YOU WEREN'T SURE</i>
<i>THAT YOU SHOULD,</i>

16:31.758 --> 16:34.192
<i>BUT I WOULDN'T GIVE UP.</i>

16:34.194 --> 16:35.660
AND "F"...?

16:37.730 --> 16:40.298
SAMMY? "F"?

16:40.300 --> 16:42.300
"FAMILY."

16:45.104 --> 16:47.672
YOU NEVER TALK
ABOUT YOUR FAMILY.

16:47.674 --> 16:49.774
I DON'T ANYMORE
HAVE FAMILY.

16:53.479 --> 16:55.446
I'M SORRY.

16:57.649 --> 17:00.051
"F" IS FOR "FRIEND."

17:00.053 --> 17:01.052
OKAY?

17:02.354 --> 17:03.788
OKAY.

17:06.258 --> 17:09.060
[SAMILA]: <i>I WAS PROBABLY</i>
<i>THE FIRST GIRL IN MY PROVINCE</i>

17:09.062 --> 17:10.628
<i>WHO LEARNED TO READ</i>
<i>AND SPEAK ENGLISH</i>

17:10.630 --> 17:12.397
<i>ON AN OLD PILLOWCASE,</i>

17:12.399 --> 17:13.631
<i>BUT I DIDN'T WANT TO</i>
<i>BE THE LAST.</i>

17:13.633 --> 17:15.466
<i>"F" EQUALS "FRIEND."</i>

17:15.468 --> 17:18.703
<i>THAT'S WHY WE STARTED</i>
<i>THE SCHOOL. REMEMBER?</i>

17:18.705 --> 17:21.205
[SAMILA]: BUZZ.

17:21.207 --> 17:23.107
PLEASE...

17:23.109 --> 17:24.475
TEACH MORE.

17:24.477 --> 17:26.377
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

17:26.379 --> 17:28.446
[♪]

17:30.516 --> 17:35.653
YOU TEACH AMERICAN ON US,
WE TEACH AFGHANISTAN ON YOU.

17:35.655 --> 17:38.456
[♪]

17:40.526 --> 17:43.161
[SAMILA]: <i>YOU WERE THE BEST</i>
<i>FRIEND I EVER HAD, BUZZ.</i>

17:43.163 --> 17:45.329
[SAMILA]:
"F" IS FOR "FRIEND."

17:45.331 --> 17:47.165
[CHILDREN]:
"F" IS FOR "FRIEND."

17:47.167 --> 17:49.700
<i>AND I HOPE YOU DIDN'T BLAME</i>
<i>YOURSELF FOR WHAT HAPPENED.</i>

17:52.771 --> 17:54.605
"G" IS FOR "GOAT."

17:54.607 --> 17:56.607
[CHILDREN]: "G" IS FOR "GOAT."

17:56.609 --> 17:58.176
[EXPLODING]

17:58.178 --> 18:00.511
EVERYBODY DOWN!
TALIBAN! TALIBAN!

18:00.513 --> 18:02.447
[SCREAMING]

18:02.449 --> 18:04.515
THEY'RE AFTER THE SCHOOL!
LET'S GO!

18:04.517 --> 18:06.417
GET THE KIDS OUT OF HERE NOW!
THEY'RE AFTER THE SCHOOL!

18:06.419 --> 18:09.420
-COME ON! RUN, RUN, RUN!
-SAMMY, RUN!

18:09.422 --> 18:11.255
GO! GO, GO, GO!

18:11.257 --> 18:12.690
SAMMY!

18:12.692 --> 18:14.425
COME ON! GO!

18:14.427 --> 18:16.694
SAMMY! SAMMY!

18:16.696 --> 18:19.130
SAMMY!

18:19.132 --> 18:21.532
[EXPLOSION ROARS]

18:25.604 --> 18:28.206
[EXPLOSION]

18:28.208 --> 18:30.842
[PANIC AND SCREAMING]

18:32.411 --> 18:33.611
BUZZ!

18:33.613 --> 18:34.712
COME ON, MAN,
WE'RE PULLING OUT!

18:34.714 --> 18:36.714
WE GOTTA GET TO THAT CHOPPER!

18:39.718 --> 18:42.487
SAMMY! SAMMY?

18:42.489 --> 18:44.889
SAMMY! SAMMY!

18:47.226 --> 18:49.360
KEEP YOUR EYES CLOSED.

18:49.362 --> 18:50.628
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY!

18:50.630 --> 18:54.265
[♪]

19:00.606 --> 19:03.307
WAIT! WAIT!

19:03.309 --> 19:04.642
WE'RE FULL! JUST YOU, BUZZ!

19:04.644 --> 19:06.277
NO! TAKE HER!
I'M STAYING.

19:06.279 --> 19:07.879
-NO WAY, MAN! GET IN!
-BUZZ!

19:07.881 --> 19:09.914
GOTTA GET HER OUT OF HERE.
PROMISE ME!

19:09.916 --> 19:12.283
THEY'LL KILL HER IF SHE STAYS!
GO. GO. GO, GO!

19:13.352 --> 19:16.154
[♪]

19:21.894 --> 19:23.895
[SAMILA]: <i>THAT'S ALL</i>
<i>I CAN REMEMBER OF THAT DAY.</i>

19:23.897 --> 19:24.896
BUZZ!

19:26.565 --> 19:29.167
<i>I NEVER WENT BACK</i>
<i>TO MY VILLAGE.</i>

19:30.502 --> 19:32.737
[OLIVER]: "I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU.

19:32.739 --> 19:35.640
"I HOPE YOU FOUND
YOUR WAY HOME.

19:35.642 --> 19:39.210
"I PRAY EVERY DAY...

19:40.679 --> 19:42.880
THAT YOU LIVED."

19:50.589 --> 19:53.858
OLIVER? ARE...

19:53.860 --> 19:55.760
ARE YOU OKAY?

20:01.934 --> 20:03.768
"I DON'T REMEMBER
VERY MUCH AFTER

20:03.770 --> 20:05.903
"YOU PUT ME
IN THE HELICOPTER.

20:05.905 --> 20:08.739
"I REMEMBER MANY AIRPLANES
AND MANY DOCTORS,

20:08.741 --> 20:11.342
"AND HOW KIND EVERYONE WAS.

20:11.344 --> 20:13.578
"I LIVE IN AMERICA NOW.

20:13.580 --> 20:15.346
"I HAVE A NEW FAMILY,

20:15.348 --> 20:16.514
"AND TODAY
I AM GOING TO COLLEGE.

20:16.516 --> 20:18.216
"I PICKED--

20:18.218 --> 20:20.218
COLORADO VISTA COLLEGE."

20:23.889 --> 20:26.224
[OLIVER]:
"BECAUSE YOU ALWAYS SAID

20:26.226 --> 20:27.825
YOU WANTED
TO GO BACK HOME."

20:29.428 --> 20:32.396
"MAYBE THIS WILL MAKE IT EASIER
TO FIND ME.

20:32.398 --> 20:33.531
"I REALLY HOPE YOU DO

20:33.533 --> 20:35.600
"BECAUSE THERE'S
SOMETHING IMPORTANT

20:35.602 --> 20:37.301
"I WANT YOU TO KNOW.

20:37.303 --> 20:39.537
LOVE, YOUR FRIEND
FOREVER..."

20:41.240 --> 20:43.708
SAMILA.

20:43.710 --> 20:45.543
SAMILA NICHOLSON.

20:45.545 --> 20:48.479
SHE IS A SENIOR
AT COLORADO VISTA COLLEGE,

20:48.481 --> 20:49.780
AND SHE GRADUATES

20:49.782 --> 20:51.415
THIS SUNDAY, AT 3:00 P.M.

20:51.417 --> 20:53.384
WHAT A GRADUATION
PRESENT IT WOULD BE

20:53.386 --> 20:55.253
IF WE FOUND BUZZ.

20:55.255 --> 20:56.854
I HAVE NO DOUBT
YOU WILL.

20:56.856 --> 20:58.456
IT MAY REQUIRE
MORE TIME IN THE FIELD.

20:58.458 --> 20:59.557
WELL, GO FOR IT!

20:59.559 --> 21:01.425
CONSIDER IT A--
WHAT DID YOU CALL IT?

21:01.427 --> 21:02.760
A LICENSE TO DELIVER.

21:02.762 --> 21:04.362
GOD, YOU'RE CUTE.

21:04.364 --> 21:06.030
YES! WE'LL KEEP HIM.

21:06.032 --> 21:08.766
[♪]

21:11.536 --> 21:14.472
[COLLEGE CHATTER
AND BUSTLE]

21:14.474 --> 21:16.040
THE REGISTRAR SAYS

21:16.042 --> 21:17.975
SHE HAS A STUDENT JOB
AT THE LIBRARY.

21:17.977 --> 21:18.943
OF COURSE SHE DOES.

21:18.945 --> 21:21.045
SHE'S A READER.

21:22.481 --> 21:24.448
I BET THAT'S HER.

21:25.550 --> 21:26.550
HI.

21:31.757 --> 21:32.890
SAMMY?

21:37.729 --> 21:40.031
EVERYBODY AROUND HERE
CALLS ME "MILA."

21:40.033 --> 21:42.500
NO ONE'S CALLED ME "SAMMY"
SINCE BUZZ.

21:42.502 --> 21:43.601
OH, I HOPE
YOU DON'T MIND.

21:43.603 --> 21:44.969
OH, OF COURSE NOT.

21:44.971 --> 21:47.571
I'VE BEEN DREAMING
ABOUT FINDING HIM FOR SO LONG.

21:47.573 --> 21:49.640
I CAN'T BELIEVE THE LETTER
NEVER EVEN GOT TO THE ARMY.

21:49.642 --> 21:53.411
AND FOR THAT,
WE DEEPLY APOLOGIZE.

21:53.413 --> 21:55.713
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE
THAT YOU COULD TELL US,

21:55.715 --> 21:57.315
ANYTHING
THAT YOU REMEMBER

21:57.317 --> 21:58.916
ABOUT BUZZ
THAT MIGHT HELP US?

22:01.853 --> 22:03.921
HE WAS KIND.

22:03.923 --> 22:05.089
[CHUCKLES]

22:05.091 --> 22:06.490
HE HAD A WONDERFUL LAUGH.

22:06.492 --> 22:07.858
HE LIKED BROWNIES.

22:07.860 --> 22:10.561
[LAUGHS] EVERYBODY
LOVED THOSE THINGS!

22:10.563 --> 22:12.830
HIS MOTHER MADE THEM
AND SENT THEM EVERY MONTH.

22:12.832 --> 22:15.066
HE CALLED THEM...
SOMETHING.

22:16.702 --> 22:17.835
[SIGHS] UM...

22:17.837 --> 22:21.806
"O" IS FOR...
"OPPORTUNITY."

22:21.808 --> 22:24.542
"P" IS FOR...

22:25.744 --> 22:27.445
"P" IS...

22:27.447 --> 22:29.347
[GASPS] "PEG'S
PRACTICALLY-PERFECT BROWNIES!"

22:29.349 --> 22:30.781
HIS MOTHER'S NAME WAS "PEG"!

22:30.783 --> 22:32.717
"PEG'S PRACTICALLY-PERFECT
BROWNIES"--

22:32.719 --> 22:35.052
OF COURSE! PEG'S
PRACTICALLY-PERFECT BROWNIES.

22:35.054 --> 22:36.020
PEG'S PRACTICALLY-
PERFECT BROWNIES.

22:36.022 --> 22:36.920
[SCATTERED GIGGLES]

22:36.922 --> 22:38.389
I'M FEELING REALLY
LEFT OUT RIGHT NOW.

22:38.391 --> 22:39.657
LOOK IT UP.
IT'S ON THE INTERNET.

22:39.659 --> 22:41.125
A COUPLE YEARS AGO,

22:41.127 --> 22:42.893
A LOST BOX CAME THROUGH
THE D.L.O.,

22:42.895 --> 22:44.061
FULL OF BROWNIES.

22:44.063 --> 22:45.830
IT WAS ADDRESSED
TO AN ARMY A.B.O. ADDRESS,

22:45.832 --> 22:48.432
WE HAD TO CONTACT THE SHIPPER
TO REROUTE THEM.

22:48.434 --> 22:50.968
RITA HAS
A PHOTOGRAPHIC MEMORY.

22:50.970 --> 22:53.137
"PEG'S PRACTICALLY-PERFECT
BROWNIE COMPANY--

22:53.139 --> 22:55.940
SEND YOUR FAVORITE SOLDIER A BOX
OF INCREDIBLY GOOD BROWNIES."

22:55.942 --> 22:57.675
OH, YES, THEY WERE.

22:57.677 --> 22:59.810
"HOMEMADE AND SHIPPED
TO ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD,

22:59.812 --> 23:01.912
"DIRECTLY FROM THE KITCHEN
OF AN ARMY MOM.

23:01.914 --> 23:03.914
"PEG PARKER
IN DENVER, COLORADO

23:03.916 --> 23:05.416
"BEGAN HER BROWNIE COMPANY

23:05.418 --> 23:06.884
"IN 2008,

23:06.886 --> 23:10.087
TO HONOR HER SON
WHO SERVED IN AFGHANISTAN."

23:10.089 --> 23:11.889
I REMEMBER NOW.
I CALLED THE SHIPPER

23:11.891 --> 23:14.492
AND TOLD HER WE HAD THE BOX
IN DEAD LETTERS.

23:14.494 --> 23:16.460
AND SHE SAID THAT WE SHOULD
JUST EAT THE BROWNIES

23:16.462 --> 23:18.529
AND THAT SHE WOULD RESEND
ANOTHER BOX--

23:18.531 --> 23:20.064
-...TO THE NEW ADDRESS.
-THAT'S BUZZ'S MOTHER?

23:20.066 --> 23:21.699
IT'S GOTTA BE.

23:21.701 --> 23:22.999
SO I GUESS WE'RE OFF

23:23.001 --> 23:26.670
TO FIND PRACTICALLY-PERFECT PEG
AND HER BROWNIES.

23:26.672 --> 23:28.773
I'D GIVEN UP IMAGINING

23:28.775 --> 23:30.574
THAT I'D EVER GET TO
SEE HIM AGAIN.

23:30.576 --> 23:32.943
WELL, WE CAN'T
MAKE ANY PROMISES,

23:32.945 --> 23:34.578
BUT WE'LL TRY.

23:34.580 --> 23:37.581
THAT WOULD BE SO... PERFECT?

23:37.583 --> 23:39.817
[EVERYONE CHUCKLES]

23:39.819 --> 23:42.620
BUT WHY ARE YOU
DOING ALL THIS?

23:42.622 --> 23:45.423
WELL, IN THIS AGE
OF TWEETS AND TEXTS

23:45.425 --> 23:46.757
AND ABBREVIATED THOUGHT,

23:46.759 --> 23:48.125
I THINK PEOPLE FOR GRANTED

23:48.127 --> 23:49.693
THE GIFT OF LEARNING
HOW TO READ AND WRITE,

23:49.695 --> 23:53.431
AND PERHAPS NOBODY
UNDERSTANDS THAT BETTER

23:53.433 --> 23:55.900
THAN THOSE OF US WHOSE JOB IT IS
TO DELIVER A LETTER.

23:57.202 --> 24:00.104
BUT THIS IS JUST ONE LETTER.

24:01.606 --> 24:02.840
NOT TO YOU.

24:02.842 --> 24:05.443
NOT TO BUZZ.

24:05.445 --> 24:07.812
[♪]

24:10.949 --> 24:12.850
WELL, THIS IS GREAT, OLIVER.

24:12.852 --> 24:14.151
-PERHAPS.
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

24:14.153 --> 24:16.720
BUZZ'S MOTHER SAID
SHE STARTED HER BUSINESS

24:16.722 --> 24:20.057
IN ORDER TO HONOR HER SON
WHO SERVED IN AFGHANISTAN.

24:21.193 --> 24:23.994
SHE DOESN'T SAY
IF HE'S STILL ALIVE.

24:28.099 --> 24:32.703
BENJAMIN WENT MISSING-IN-ACTION
FOR ALMOST A YEAR.

24:32.705 --> 24:35.706
HE WAS INJURED
IN SOME SORT OF ATTACK,

24:35.708 --> 24:37.208
BUT HE NEVER TALKED ABOUT IT.

24:37.210 --> 24:39.210
DID YOU EVER
CALL HIM BUZZ?

24:39.212 --> 24:40.644
NO.

24:40.646 --> 24:43.614
SOME OF HIS ARMY BUDDIES DID.

24:43.616 --> 24:45.115
BUT AFTER HE GOT BACK,
HE NEVER MENTIONED THEM.

24:45.117 --> 24:47.585
IS THIS HIM?

24:47.587 --> 24:49.687
[PEGGY]: YEAH.
THAT'S JUST BEFORE HE ENLISTED.

24:49.689 --> 24:50.821
HE LOOKS SO SWEET.

24:50.823 --> 24:52.923
OH, HE WAS ALWAYS
A SWEET BOY.

24:52.925 --> 24:54.558
MRS. PARKER,
DO YOU KNOW WHERE

24:54.560 --> 24:56.527
WE MIGHT BE ABLE
TO FIND BENJAMIN?

24:57.796 --> 24:59.930
[VOICE TREMBLES]:
I DON'T KNOW.

25:01.132 --> 25:05.002
I NEVER THOUGHT
THAT I WOULD SAY THAT

25:05.004 --> 25:06.237
ABOUT MY OWN SON.

25:08.006 --> 25:10.641
SOMETHING HAPPENED
BACK THERE,

25:10.643 --> 25:14.745
AND WHEN I FINALLY
GOT HIM BACK...

25:17.649 --> 25:20.684
HE WAS SOMEBODY ELSE.

25:21.686 --> 25:23.754
HE WAS SO...

25:23.756 --> 25:26.023
RESTLESS,
ALWAYS ON THE MOVE,

25:26.025 --> 25:31.295
AND HE STARTED DISAPPEARING
FOR DAYS AT A TIME,

25:31.297 --> 25:33.230
AND, FINALLY, ONE DAY,
HE JUST...

25:33.232 --> 25:36.700
WELL, NEVER CAME BACK HOME.

25:38.236 --> 25:40.905
AND WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU HEARD FROM HIM?

25:40.907 --> 25:43.574
HE CALLED ME
ALMOST A YEAR AGO.

25:43.576 --> 25:45.643
IT WAS ON MY BIRTHDAY.

25:45.645 --> 25:48.812
DID HE GIVE YOU
AN ADDRESS OR--

25:48.814 --> 25:52.016
I ASKED HIM WHERE I COULD
SEND HIM SOME BROWNIES, AND...

25:54.920 --> 25:58.322
HE WAS QUIET FOR SO LONG,
I THOUGHT HE'D HUNG UP.

25:59.858 --> 26:03.127
AND THEN HE SAID,
"DON'T.

26:03.129 --> 26:05.629
I DON'T DESERVE THEM."

26:08.633 --> 26:11.569
AND THEN HE DID HANG UP.

26:11.571 --> 26:15.739
AND THAT'S THE, UH,
THE LAST I HEARD FROM HIM.

26:18.143 --> 26:21.145
WHAT COULD HE BE SO ASHAMED OF
THAT HE CAN'T COME HOME?

26:21.147 --> 26:24.014
NOTHING.

26:28.219 --> 26:30.220
[♪]

26:31.690 --> 26:34.758
YOU TAKE SOME OF THESE,
AND, UH--

26:34.760 --> 26:36.360
WHEN YOU FIND HIM,

26:36.362 --> 26:39.129
YOU TELL HIM HE CAN ALWAYS
COME HOME FOR MORE.

26:39.131 --> 26:41.165
ALWAYS.

26:41.167 --> 26:43.033
CORPORAL BENJAMIN PARKER.

26:43.035 --> 26:47.171
SERVED IN NURISTAN PROVINCE,
BEGINNING IN 2003.

26:47.173 --> 26:49.139
GOT INTO A FIREFIGHT
THE FOLLOWING YEAR,

26:49.141 --> 26:51.742
WENT M.I.A. FOR NINE MONTHS.

26:51.744 --> 26:54.078
EXTRACTION DETAILS
ARE CLASSIFIED,

26:54.080 --> 26:56.880
BUT HE DID SPEND SEVERAL MONTHS

26:56.882 --> 26:59.750
AT A V.A. HOSPITAL
IN WASHINGTON.

26:59.752 --> 27:01.952
RECEIVED AN HONORABLE
MEDICAL DISCHARGE,

27:01.954 --> 27:04.355
COLLECTED
A FEW V.A. BENEFITS

27:04.357 --> 27:09.026
IN 2006, '07, AND '08...

27:09.028 --> 27:10.094
[CLICKS KEY]

27:10.096 --> 27:12.162
THEN DROPPED OFF THE MAP.

27:12.164 --> 27:14.632
AND THE FIREFIGHT?

27:14.634 --> 27:16.233
CLASSIFIED.

27:16.235 --> 27:19.803
BUT THE CASUALTIES
WERE MILITARY AND CIVILIAN.

27:19.805 --> 27:21.138
ANYTHING ELSE?

27:21.140 --> 27:23.240
ONE NOTE ON HIS RECORD--

27:23.242 --> 27:27.311
HE RECEIVED HIS PURPLE HEART
WHILE CONVALESCING,

27:27.313 --> 27:30.748
BUT LEFT IT ON HIS BED
WHEN HE WAS DISCHARGED.

27:30.750 --> 27:32.282
CAPTAIN,
WE ARE NOT PREPARED

27:32.284 --> 27:34.184
TO GIVE UP
TRYING TO FIND HIM.

27:34.186 --> 27:36.854
HE GAVE UP TOO MUCH
TO SERVE HIS COUNTRY.

27:39.090 --> 27:41.392
[QUIET, RELUCTANT SIGH]

27:43.194 --> 27:44.294
THERE'S A FRIEND OF MINE--

27:44.296 --> 27:46.730
THINK I'VE KNOWN HIM
SINCE BOOT CAMP--

27:46.732 --> 27:49.199
HE RUNS A MINISTRY
TO VETS,

27:49.201 --> 27:51.902
AND HE'S COME THROUGH
FOR ME BEFORE.

27:51.904 --> 27:53.437
OLIVER?

27:53.439 --> 27:55.339
PASTOR PERRY.
PLEASURE TO MEET YOU.

27:55.341 --> 27:57.174
THIS IS MY COLLEAGUE,
MS. McINERNEY.

27:57.176 --> 27:58.742
-HOW DO YOU DO?
-HI.

27:58.744 --> 28:00.411
WELL, YOU HAVE
GOOD TIMING.

28:00.413 --> 28:03.180
HE DOESN'T HAVE
REGULAR HOURS.

28:03.182 --> 28:04.882
RIGHT NOW, HE'S BACK
WORKING FOR US FOR AWHILE.

28:07.152 --> 28:09.286
[♪]

28:13.224 --> 28:14.758
THANK YOU.

28:14.760 --> 28:16.160
YOU'RE WELCOME.

28:20.699 --> 28:21.765
MR. PARKER?

28:25.737 --> 28:27.371
BENJAMIN?

28:38.283 --> 28:40.017
BUZZ?

28:50.261 --> 28:52.029
[OLIVER]:
THIS MUST BE A...

28:52.031 --> 28:53.464
A GREAT DEAL TO TAKE IN

28:53.466 --> 28:55.132
AFTER SO LONG.

28:55.134 --> 28:57.301
YEAH.

28:57.303 --> 28:59.236
THERE'S MORE.

29:08.480 --> 29:10.414
THAT LETTER IS, UH...

29:10.416 --> 29:12.983
FOUR YEARS OLD.

29:12.985 --> 29:17.521
SAMMY IS ABOUT TO GRADUATE
FROM COLLEGE THIS WEEKEND,

29:17.523 --> 29:20.057
AND SHE'D LIKE YOU TO BE THERE.

29:24.129 --> 29:26.296
WE MET HER, BUZZ.

29:26.298 --> 29:28.332
SHE'S SMART

29:28.334 --> 29:30.367
AND BEAUTIFUL,

29:30.369 --> 29:32.436
AND WHEN YOU LOOK AT HER,

29:32.438 --> 29:35.339
YOU CAN'T HELP
BUT GET THIS FEELING

29:35.341 --> 29:37.241
THAT SHE'S GONNA
MAKE A DIFFERENCE IN THIS WORLD

29:37.243 --> 29:39.243
SOMEDAY...

29:41.312 --> 29:43.814
AND THAT'S BECAUSE OF YOU.

29:43.816 --> 29:46.150
BECAUSE OF ME?

29:49.888 --> 29:51.955
I TAUGHT HER HOW TO READ.

29:51.957 --> 29:54.057
I LET HER START A SCHOOL.

29:55.260 --> 29:58.028
I MADE HER A TARGET.

29:58.030 --> 30:00.497
AND LOOK WHAT HAPPENED,
TO ALL OF THEM...

30:03.168 --> 30:05.869
[SOBS]: BECAUSE OF ME.

30:05.871 --> 30:07.237
BUZZ...

30:07.239 --> 30:11.809
THERE'S NO EASY ANSWER
TO WHAT HAPPENED THAT DAY.

30:12.944 --> 30:15.379
YOU TRIED TO BE A PEACEMAKER

30:15.381 --> 30:19.216
AND THE AWFUL INSANITY OF WAR

30:19.218 --> 30:21.451
DID EVERYTHING
IT COULD TO STOP YOU.

30:21.453 --> 30:23.587
AND BECAUSE OF THAT...

30:23.589 --> 30:25.189
[BUZZ SOBBING]

30:25.191 --> 30:28.425
YOU THINK YOU DON'T DESERVE
SAMMY'S GRATITUDE?

30:28.427 --> 30:31.328
OR A PURPLE HEART?

30:31.330 --> 30:34.231
OR A GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP
IN YOUR OWN BED?

30:34.233 --> 30:38.502
BUZZ, ANY MAN WHO PUTS
HIS LIFE ON THE LINE

30:38.504 --> 30:41.038
TO STAND BETWEEN WHAT IS RIGHT
AND WHAT IS WRONG

30:41.040 --> 30:43.841
DESERVES THANKS
FROM THE ONES HE DEFENDS.

30:45.376 --> 30:49.279
UNTIL YOU REACHED OUT
AND GAVE A LITTLE GIRL

30:49.281 --> 30:54.351
A PAIR OF SOCKS
AND A BOOK ON A PILLOWCASE,

30:54.353 --> 30:58.422
SAMMY WOKE UP EVERY MORNING
WITH NOTHING TO LOOK FORWARD TO

30:58.424 --> 31:00.891
BUT MORE POVERTY,
MORE VIOLENCE.

31:04.295 --> 31:06.330
YOU GAVE HER SOMETHING
TO DREAM ABOUT.

31:08.166 --> 31:10.367
YOU SACRIFICED YOURSELF

31:10.369 --> 31:13.303
TO GIVE HER A FUTURE
AND A HOPE.

31:13.305 --> 31:15.572
THAT IS NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

31:19.310 --> 31:21.912
IT'S SOMETHING TO CELEBRATE.

31:29.654 --> 31:32.356
WE WANT TO
HELP YOU DO THAT.

31:34.058 --> 31:36.460
[♪]

31:45.970 --> 31:49.640
THERE'S NO PLACE LIKE HOME.
THERE'S NO PLACE LIKE HOME.

31:49.642 --> 31:52.542
EVERYTHING
YOU NEED, DOROTHY,

31:52.544 --> 31:55.679
IS RIGHT THERE
ON YOUR SHOES...

31:55.681 --> 31:57.247
NO, NO.
"IN YOUR SHO--"

31:57.249 --> 31:58.448
NO. "ON YOUR FEE--"

31:58.450 --> 32:00.617
HOW AM I
GOING TO GET THIS?

32:00.619 --> 32:02.085
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.
JUST TRY IT AGAIN.

32:02.087 --> 32:04.087
OKAY.

32:05.490 --> 32:07.291
OKAY, EVERYBODY,
WE'VE GOT A...

32:09.961 --> 32:11.495
WHAT'S THIS?

32:11.497 --> 32:13.497
[RUMBLING]

32:13.499 --> 32:15.032
AND WHAT'S THAT?

32:15.034 --> 32:17.000
THIS IS THE FLOATING WORKSPACE
THAT I MADE FOR YOU,

32:17.002 --> 32:19.002
AND-AND THAT IS GLINDA
THE GOOD WITCH OF THE NORTH.

32:19.004 --> 32:20.037
GUESS WHAT?

32:20.039 --> 32:21.638
MRS. HANSEN HAS GOUT!

32:21.640 --> 32:24.975
AH! GREAT.

32:24.977 --> 32:27.978
CONGRATULATIONS,
THERESA.

32:27.980 --> 32:29.346
AND THANK YOU,
NORMAN,

32:29.348 --> 32:31.014
FOR MY VERY INTERESTING...

32:31.016 --> 32:32.716
FLOATING... THING.

32:32.718 --> 32:36.086
UH, BUT, AT THE MOMENT,
WE HAVE A PROBLEM.

32:36.088 --> 32:37.254
THERE ARE
NO PROBLEMS, DARLING,

32:37.256 --> 32:39.957
ONLY OPPORTUNITIES
IN DISGUISE.

32:39.959 --> 32:41.558
OH, THIS ONE'S IN DISGUISE.

32:41.560 --> 32:45.329
EVERYONE.
THIS IS BUZZ.

32:45.331 --> 32:48.198
HE NEEDS TO GET READY
FOR SAMILA'S GRADUATION,

32:48.200 --> 32:50.200
WHICH IS IN THREE HOURS.

32:51.536 --> 32:52.970
PIECE OF CAKE.

32:52.972 --> 32:54.538
THEY DON'T
CALL ME A GODDESS

32:54.540 --> 32:56.206
IN THE POSTAL PANTHEON
FOR NOTHIN'.

32:56.208 --> 32:58.208
NOW, WHAT
ARE YOU, HONEY?

32:58.210 --> 33:00.677
A, UH, 40-REGULAR?

33:00.679 --> 33:03.513
SHANE, THERE IS A VINTAGE SHOP
ON LARIMER.

33:03.515 --> 33:05.148
GOT IT.

33:05.150 --> 33:07.584
OLIVER, WE'RE GONNA NEED
SOME SHAVING CREAM AND A RAZOR.

33:07.586 --> 33:09.186
-RIGHT.
-RITA?

33:09.188 --> 33:12.222
GET ME SOME HOT TOWELS
FROM THE WOMEN'S LOCKER ROOM,

33:12.224 --> 33:13.223
AND NORMAN...

33:13.225 --> 33:14.257
YOU CAN KEEP US COMPANY.

33:14.259 --> 33:16.093
COME.

33:16.095 --> 33:18.195
THIS IS GONNA BE
FUN, BUZZ.

33:18.197 --> 33:19.663
OH! I KNOW WHAT I NEED.

33:23.234 --> 33:25.135
ARE YOU HUNGRY?

33:25.137 --> 33:27.037
[CHUCKLES] A LITTLE.

33:27.039 --> 33:30.307
THEY REALLY ARE
PRACTICALLY PERFECT, YOU KNOW.

33:30.309 --> 33:32.175
HERE WE GO!

33:32.177 --> 33:34.011
NOW BUCKLE UP, HONEY.

33:34.013 --> 33:36.346
IT'S SHOWTIME!

33:40.785 --> 33:43.453
[APPLAUDING]

33:44.722 --> 33:46.723
MICHAEL CARTER MATTHEWS.

33:48.693 --> 33:50.761
[APPLAUDING]

33:53.731 --> 33:55.298
[POPPING]

33:55.300 --> 33:56.366
[LAUGHTER AND APPLAUSE]

33:56.368 --> 33:58.502
ALONA KAREEN MORGAN.

33:58.504 --> 34:00.470
[CROWD APPLAUDS]

34:01.539 --> 34:03.507
THERE SHE IS.

34:03.509 --> 34:06.276
SAMILA KAMDESH NICHOLSON.

34:06.278 --> 34:07.577
[APPLAUDING]

34:07.579 --> 34:09.613
[♪]

34:11.449 --> 34:14.084
MY GOD, SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

34:14.086 --> 34:15.786
AND GUESS WHAT?

34:15.788 --> 34:18.055
SHE'S VALEDICTORIAN.

34:20.725 --> 34:22.592
[♪]

34:22.594 --> 34:24.261
[CHUCKLING]

34:25.797 --> 34:28.198
THERE'S REALLY
NO ONE HERE TODAY

34:28.200 --> 34:29.366
WHO WILL UNDERSTAND

34:29.368 --> 34:31.068
WHAT WEARING ONE SOCK

34:31.070 --> 34:33.136
AND RECEIVING
A COLLEGE DEGREE

34:33.138 --> 34:34.471
HAVE IN COMMON.

34:34.473 --> 34:36.339
NO ONE...

34:36.341 --> 34:42.245
EXCEPT THE ONE MAN
WHO MADE BOTH OF THESE POSSIBLE.

34:42.247 --> 34:44.081
I CALLED HIM "BUZZ,"

34:44.083 --> 34:46.750
ALTHOUGH...

34:46.752 --> 34:49.352
I NEVER KNEW HIS REAL NAME.

34:51.656 --> 34:53.757
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
IF HE IS STILL ALIVE.

34:55.860 --> 34:59.763
HE WAS THE AMERICAN SOLDIER
WHO TAUGHT ME TO SPEAK ENGLISH,

34:59.765 --> 35:01.364
TO READ,

35:01.366 --> 35:02.666
AND TO WRITE.

35:02.668 --> 35:06.636
HE WAS THE FRIEND
WHOSE KINDNESS CONVINCED ME

35:06.638 --> 35:08.872
THAT THERE WAS MORE TO LIFE

35:08.874 --> 35:11.775
THAN COLLECTING
USED SHELL CASINGS

35:11.777 --> 35:13.743
FROM THE GROUND
IN AFGHANISTAN

35:13.745 --> 35:16.413
TO TRADE FOR FOOD.

35:16.415 --> 35:18.348
BUZZ INSPIRED ME

35:18.350 --> 35:20.283
TO IMAGINE
WHAT I COULD BECOME...

35:20.285 --> 35:24.554
INSTEAD OF FEAR
WHAT MIGHT BECOME OF ME.

35:25.656 --> 35:28.892
AND BECAUSE OF HIM...

35:28.894 --> 35:30.092
[CHOKES UP]: I LIVED...

35:30.094 --> 35:33.997
TO FIND TWO PARENTS
AND A BROTHER TO LOVE ME.

35:34.532 --> 35:36.533
I LIVED

35:36.535 --> 35:39.136
TO USE THE WORDS
HE GAVE ME

35:39.138 --> 35:42.706
TO EXPRESS MY LOVE
AND MY DREAMS,

35:42.708 --> 35:44.341
TO MAKE FRIENDS...

35:46.677 --> 35:48.678
AND, LIKE HIM...

35:48.680 --> 35:50.680
TO MAKE PEACE.

35:50.682 --> 35:52.749
IF I COULD,

35:52.751 --> 35:55.252
I WOULD TELL BUZZ

35:55.254 --> 35:58.522
THAT THOSE WORDS GAVE HOPE
NOT JUST TO ME,

35:58.524 --> 36:00.457
BUT TO DOZENS
OF OTHER CHILDREN--

36:00.459 --> 36:01.858
INNER-CITY CHILDREN

36:01.860 --> 36:04.728
THAT I HAVE HAD THE PRIVILEGE
TO TEACH

36:04.730 --> 36:07.831
AS A STUDENT TEACHER
HERE IN COLORADO.

36:07.833 --> 36:13.236
AND EVEN THOUGH HE IS NOT HERE
TO STAND AND BE RECOGNIZED,

36:13.238 --> 36:14.404
THOSE CHILDREN

36:14.406 --> 36:15.739
ARE HERE
TO STAND FOR HIM.

36:17.308 --> 36:19.809
[♪]

36:22.446 --> 36:24.915
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

36:34.559 --> 36:36.927
FELLOW STUDENTS...

36:36.929 --> 36:40.664
TODAY IS A BEGINNING
FOR ALL OF US,

36:40.666 --> 36:43.466
AND MAY WE ALWAYS
REMEMBER THAT,

36:43.468 --> 36:45.468
WHEREVER WE GO FROM HERE,

36:45.470 --> 36:50.640
IT WILL BE BECAUSE OF THE GIFTS
AND SACRIFICE OF OTHERS.

36:50.642 --> 36:53.310
SOME WE HAVE KNOWN
ALL OUR LIVES...

36:54.412 --> 36:58.615
SOME WE MAY NEVER SEE AGAIN...

36:58.617 --> 37:00.617
BUT ALL OF THEM...

37:00.619 --> 37:02.953
[♪]

37:05.523 --> 37:07.824
[QUIETLY]:
WE SHALL LOVE FOREVER.

37:07.826 --> 37:08.892
[GASPS]

37:13.864 --> 37:15.966
[CROWD APPLAUDING]

37:22.673 --> 37:25.542
[♪]

37:37.655 --> 37:40.523
EVERYBODY SAY "CHEESE."

37:40.525 --> 37:42.025
[TOGETHER]:
CHEESE!

37:43.628 --> 37:44.628
I SHOULD
PROBABLY GET GOING.

37:44.630 --> 37:45.862
I DON'T WANT TO
BARGE IN

37:45.864 --> 37:47.364
ON YOUR BIG DAY
WITH YOUR FAMILY.

37:47.366 --> 37:49.899
"F" IS FOR FAMILY.

37:49.901 --> 37:51.935
[CHUCKLES]

37:53.037 --> 37:54.304
BENJAMIN PARKER?

37:54.306 --> 37:56.406
YES, SIR.

37:56.408 --> 37:58.842
WELCOME HOME, CORPORAL.

38:01.812 --> 38:03.980
WE THINK YOU MIGHT HAVE
FORGOTTEN THIS.

38:12.056 --> 38:15.058
DON'T FORGET
WHO YOU ARE, SON.

38:15.060 --> 38:18.328
AND I PROMISE,
WE WON'T FORGET, EITHER.

38:18.330 --> 38:20.063
THANK YOU, SIR.

38:21.332 --> 38:23.900
[♪]

38:27.038 --> 38:29.439
[THEATER CROWD APPLAUDING]

38:32.710 --> 38:34.978
[APPLAUSE CONTINUES]

38:34.980 --> 38:38.448
AH! WHAT DID YOU THINK?

38:38.450 --> 38:39.983
BRAVA!

38:39.985 --> 38:43.353
WHAT DID YOU THINK?
WHAT DID YOU THINK?

38:43.355 --> 38:44.587
WAS I OKAY?

38:44.589 --> 38:45.955
I WAS SO NERVOUS.

38:45.957 --> 38:47.524
YOU WOULDN'T KNOW IT.

38:47.526 --> 38:48.758
YOU WERE AMAZING.

38:48.760 --> 38:51.728
IT WAS REALLY...
YOU WERE REALLY QUITE SOMETHING.

38:51.730 --> 38:54.364
THEN I WAS GOOD?

38:54.366 --> 38:55.665
BEYOND GOOD.

38:55.667 --> 38:57.567
THEN THAT'S IT.

38:57.569 --> 38:59.369
WHAT'S IT?

38:59.371 --> 39:01.738
I AM QUITTING THE POST OFFICE
AND I AM GOING ON THE ROAD.

39:01.740 --> 39:02.872
[LAUGHS] WHAT?

39:02.874 --> 39:04.541
I'VE DELIVERED
MY LAST LETTER, OLIVER,

39:04.543 --> 39:06.710
AND I AM GOING
INTO SHOW BUSINESS.

39:06.712 --> 39:07.910
HOW CAN YOU
QUIT THE POST OFFICE?

39:07.912 --> 39:09.479
-YOU ARE THE POST OFFICE!
-YOU'RE THERESA CAPODIAMONTE!

39:09.481 --> 39:10.914
YOU'RE A LEGEND!

39:10.916 --> 39:11.981
I'M OUTTA HERE.

39:11.983 --> 39:13.817
IT'S TIME TO FLY!

39:13.819 --> 39:16.553
BUT WHAT ABOUT
OLIVER'S EVALUATION?

39:16.555 --> 39:17.687
YOU STILL NEED
TO TURN IT IN.

39:17.689 --> 39:19.422
OH, I FINISHED THAT YESTERDAY,

39:19.424 --> 39:20.924
AND I GAVE HIM...

39:20.926 --> 39:23.626
A SCORE OF 100%.

39:23.628 --> 39:25.862
100% ON
A PERFORMANCE REPORT?

39:25.864 --> 39:28.098
THAT'S NEVER
HAPPENED BEFORE!

39:28.100 --> 39:29.899
I'M, UH, I'M OVERWHELMED.

39:29.901 --> 39:33.069
IT WAS ALWAYS RIGHT THERE
IN YOUR POWER.

39:33.071 --> 39:36.005
YOU JUST NEEDED TO RISK IT ALL

39:36.007 --> 39:38.408
IN ORDER
TO FIND IT FOR YOURSELF.

39:38.410 --> 39:40.043
DEAR SHANE, DON'T FORGET

39:40.045 --> 39:42.045
TO GET YOUR HEAD
OUT OF THAT COMPUTER

39:42.047 --> 39:43.747
AND DANCE A LITTLE.

39:43.749 --> 39:45.415
AND RITA?

39:45.417 --> 39:48.151
THAT INCREDIBLE MEMORY
THAT YOU HAVE FOR THE PAST--

39:48.153 --> 39:49.619
IT'S NOTHING

39:49.621 --> 39:52.555
COMPARED TO THAT
TECHNICOLOR FUTURE OF YOURS,

